01:14.701 --> 01:17.102
Wow.

01:17.103 --> 01:20.639
It's really getting
kind of late.

01:20.640 --> 01:23.008
Why don't you two
get some sleep?

01:25.045 --> 01:26.578
Ben, you didn't even
touch your dinner.

01:26.579 --> 01:28.580
You want me to make you
a sandwich or something?

01:28.581 --> 01:31.417
Thank you, Betty, but,
uh, I'm still not hungry.

01:33.053 --> 01:35.821
Well, all right, then.

01:35.822 --> 01:37.856
How about everybody
just says good night?

01:37.857 --> 01:40.726
Good night.
Good night.

01:40.727 --> 01:44.563
Leo, come on, honey.

01:44.564 --> 01:46.932
It's not so bad.
I mean, there are worse problems

01:46.933 --> 01:49.968
than-- than Ben and Adrian.

01:49.969 --> 01:52.738
I mean, it's all gonna
work itself out.

01:52.739 --> 01:55.441
You'll see.

01:55.442 --> 01:57.976
All right. Well,
I'm gonna say good night.

02:00.046 --> 02:02.047
Good night.

02:02.048 --> 02:05.884
And I just wanna say
that I love you both,

02:05.885 --> 02:09.488
and I don't want
either of you to say,
"I love you, too, Betty,"

02:09.489 --> 02:11.323
because if you love me,

02:11.324 --> 02:13.592
you would take my advice
and you would sleep on it.

02:17.364 --> 02:19.098
Good night.

02:28.775 --> 02:30.709
I remember when
I said that to George

02:30.710 --> 02:32.311
when you and Amy
wanted to get married.

02:34.547 --> 02:36.215
I told them
there were worse problems

02:36.216 --> 02:37.883
than two teenagers
getting married

02:37.884 --> 02:40.352
and having a baby.

02:40.353 --> 02:42.688
I'm glad Betty
reminded me of that.

02:42.689 --> 02:45.657
There are worse problems.

02:45.658 --> 02:47.893
You're not sick.
I'm not sick.

02:47.894 --> 02:49.895
Betty's not sick.

02:49.896 --> 02:53.065
No one's sick.
You're not on drugs.

02:53.066 --> 02:54.733
You don't have a problem
with alcohol.

02:54.734 --> 02:56.902
You're not flunking
out of school.

02:56.903 --> 02:59.705
You didn't wreck the car
and get hurt
or hurt someone else.

03:01.307 --> 03:03.976
Business is good.
The company's doing well.

03:05.945 --> 03:09.314
And I have a lovely bride
upstairs who's waiting for me.

03:09.315 --> 03:12.050
And I do love her.

03:12.051 --> 03:15.120
So let's take Betty's advice
and sleep on this.

03:19.192 --> 03:21.894
[sighs]
And tomorrow,
you talk to Adrian.

03:21.895 --> 03:24.129
About what?
Dad, I already told you.

03:24.130 --> 03:26.231
She doesn't want me to know.
But you do know.

03:26.232 --> 03:28.000
I do, but I don't.

03:28.001 --> 03:29.835
No. You do,
but you don't want to.

03:29.836 --> 03:31.236
No, I don't.

03:31.237 --> 03:33.639
And that's Adrian's decision
for me not to know.

03:33.640 --> 03:36.975
And whatever she decides
to do about...this

03:36.976 --> 03:38.477
is her decision.

03:38.478 --> 03:40.412
And that way,
you don't have to be involved.

03:40.413 --> 03:41.747
I know that's what
you're thinking.

03:41.748 --> 03:42.981
I admitted
that's what I'm thinking.

03:42.982 --> 03:44.183
I don't wanna be involved.

03:44.184 --> 03:46.819
And what happens if Adrian
decides to have the baby?

03:46.820 --> 03:49.254
You gonna get involved then?
She's not going to do that.

03:49.255 --> 03:51.290
You never know, son.
What if she does?

03:51.291 --> 03:52.925
She won't.
She might.

03:52.926 --> 03:55.093
So do like I told you
and talk to her tomorrow.

03:56.496 --> 03:58.163
And keep talking to her.

03:58.164 --> 04:01.834
And keep talking to me,
and I'll keep talking to you.

04:01.835 --> 04:04.870
I love you, Ben,
and I feel for you and Adrian,

04:04.871 --> 04:05.804
but...

04:08.041 --> 04:09.441
I'm not gonna say it.

04:09.442 --> 04:11.176
You mean you're not
gonna say it again.

04:11.177 --> 04:14.413
You're just as responsible
as Adrian is for what happened.

04:14.414 --> 04:17.082
I may be just as responsible
as Adrian for what happened,

04:17.083 --> 04:19.418
but what she does
about what happened
is up to her.

04:19.418 --> 04:21.053
And you're gonna go
running off to Amy

04:21.053 --> 04:23.288
and leave Adrian
to hdle this all by herself

04:23.289 --> 04:25.057
because you're not
supposed to know anything?

04:25.058 --> 04:26.225
Yep.

04:26.226 --> 04:28.894
Are you gonna let Amy
find out from someone else?

04:28.895 --> 04:30.629
Are you?
Are you gonna tell her?

04:30.630 --> 04:32.331
I don't know
if she has to find out.

04:32.332 --> 04:34.833
I mean,
you wouldn't have found out
if I hadn't told you.

04:34.834 --> 04:37.069
What do you want from me?
I want you to tell Amy,

04:37.070 --> 04:38.904
and I want you to be
as kind to Adrian

04:38.905 --> 04:41.073
as you were to Amy
when she was in this situation.

04:41.074 --> 04:43.075
That's what I want.
Oh, no, no, no, no.

04:43.076 --> 04:44.910
You don't want me to be
so kind to Adrian

04:44.911 --> 04:47.546
as to offer to marry her
like I did Amy, do you?

04:47.547 --> 04:49.748
I mean, you can't
possibly think that.

04:49.749 --> 04:52.217
Yeah, well,
maybe I do think that.

04:52.218 --> 04:53.886
Good night.

04:54.988 --> 04:57.055
This can't be happening.

04:58.157 --> 04:59.658
[chuckles]

05:02.495 --> 05:04.863
 Falling in love 

05:04.864 --> 05:08.033
Is such an easy thing to do

05:08.034 --> 05:10.969
 Birds can do it We can do it

05:10.970 --> 05:15.374
 Let's stop talking Let's get to it,
Let's fall in love...

